Level 7 ğŸš©

Objective- Find a unknown file store in the current directory of the webpage that has password stored in it. 

Vulnerability- Injection Attack 

Description- We can use a command line vulnerability to get the list of files in the current directory, Then simply access the webpage that stores the password. 

Evidence- Attacker used a command line injection in the view query of the webpage, This command ran a query with all the information and a list of files inside this directory.  

What I learned â€“ How command line injections can manipulate data querying and potentially hand sensitive information to the attackers. I have also learned different types of command injections. Input validation could block some shell commands from executing. This along with sanitizing the output, would stop shell commands from being executed and display any output.   

Level 8 ğŸš© 

