Vulnerability- Server Side Includes (SSI) attacks  

Description- When we enter a username it gets stored in tmp file with .shtml extension, we simply send a SSI that runs the command to list files inside the directory.  

Evidence â€“ We run <! --#exec cmd =â€ls ../â€ --> this will run after the user has clicked submit button, and returns a the list of all files under current directory. Then simple editing the URL to add the file path gives us access to the password. 

What I learned â€“ Disabling  server-side includes would significantly drop the risk of SSI attacks. Make the storage path hidden on the client-side.  

Level 9 ğŸš© 

