Level 10 ğŸš© 

Objective- View and edit cookie to gain access. 

Vulnerability â€“ Cookie Manipulation 

Description-Here we have a password field only on the page, In order to gain access we must edit the cookies. Also we donâ€™t need any password or password file in this level.  

Evidence- We inspect the page and enter application tab of developer page, there we can find cookies folder wherein cookie is stored we only need to change current sessionsâ€™ cookie to gain access. In order to do so we simply change the value of cookie to yes from being a no.  

What I learned -  Server side sessions handles this vulnerability, as the session management is handled on the server and cant be manipulated. In addition to this, using encrypted cookies instead of plain text cookies makes it much more difficulty to read and write any changes to it.  

